full_text: If and when you offer advice or opinion on (discrete) mental health / mental illness / mental fitness / resilience & wellbeing.  Please spare a thought for how what you say might come across to somebody who lives through experiences similar to those which I have just described.
full_text(utf-8): b'If and when you offer advice or opinion on (discrete) mental health / mental illness / mental fitness / resilience & wellbeing.  Please spare a thought for how what you say might come across to somebody who lives through experiences similar to those which I have just described.'

full_text:
I'm not knocking people for sharing what they do to prevent or fix feeling down, or having a low mood!  To do so is healthy.

But all I ask is that if you didn't already, you might now consider that mental illness isn't just a bit of an extension to the everyday emotional range.
full_text(utf-8): b"I'm not knocking people for sharing what they do to prevent or fix feeling down, or having a low mood!  To do so is healthy.\n\nBut all I ask is that if you didn't already, you might now consider that mental illness isn't just a bit of an extension to the everyday emotional range."

full_text:
The point of this all being to illustrate that, whilst experiences vary, there *are* explicit differences between depression (just one of many examples of mental illness) and feeling a bit down.

I still get down at times.  Compared w/ depression I'm grateful to 'just' feel down.
full_text(utf-8): b"The point of this all being to illustrate that, whilst experiences vary, there *are* explicit differences between depression (just one of many examples of mental illness) and feeling a bit down.\n\nI still get down at times. The depressed moment itself:

Grim.  Really fucking grim.  Illogical thinking detached from reality.

Rob's mind: "What's the point in anything?  Why won't my wife please just fuck off?  It's okay though, I'll sort a divorce sometime soon.  When I can be bothered to do anything".

And yes, we own a dishwasher...

But seriously, to reduce the metaphor to real life: 'Moments' will strike anywhere, anytime, and sometimes with very little notice.

full_text:
*Much* less common for me nowadays, thankfully!  Due to well practised coping mechanisms.

What's far more likely is waking up with an average, or even good mood.  Then being stood by the sink washing up plates, and noticing through the kitchen window that the dog is approaching.

full_text:
Buildup - can come from nowhere!

Potentially wake up knowing, to borrow the metaphor, that the black dog is well and truly already out of his bed and trying to keep me from leaving mine.  Probably thinking something along the lines of "Oh I'm awake.  So I'm still alive".  *Numb*

full_text:

full_text: @beltfedgob @Fromtheranks You make an interesting point with 'hypnotised by power'.  That's a very powerful concept, subliminally.  Everybody can convince themselves that "I will always speak truth to power"... but in reality it's v. difficult.  Too easy to find yourself browbeaten or agreeing with rank.
full_text(utf-8): b'@beltfedgob @Fromtheranks You make an interesting point with \'hypnotised by power\'.  That\'s a very powerful concept, subliminally.  Everybody can convince themselves that "I will always speak truth to power"... but in reality it\'s v. difficult.  Too easy to find yourself browbeaten or agreeing with rank.'

full_text:
@beltfedgob @Fromtheranks It's a useful tool to instil and reinforce military hierarchy (which as I said, I don't disagree with) at the point in a career where it probably most needs instilling and reinforcing. 

It doesn't have to = bullshit and isn't mutually exclusive with proper teaching and coaching.
full_text(utf-8): b"@beltfedgob @Fromtheranks It's a useful tool to instil and reinforce military hierarchy (which as I said, I don't disagree with) at the point in a career where it probably most needs instilling and reinforcing. \n\nIt doesn't have to = bullshit and isn't mutually exclusive with proper teaching and coaching."

full_text:
@beltfedgob @Fromtheranks Perhaps in an infantry battalion a private soldier *should* call everybody by rank and surname.  I don't know.  I've not lived or studied it.

However I think that in a lot of HQs, less everyday salutey-Sir-Ma'amness would probably lead to more honest briefing of senior officers.
full_text(utf-8): b"@beltfedgob @Fromtheranks Perhaps in an infantry battalion a private soldier *should* call everybody by rank and surname.  I don't know.  I've not lived or studied it.\n\nHowever I think that in a lot of HQs, less everyday salutey-Sir-Ma'amness would probably lead to more honest briefing of senior officers."

full_text: @beltfedgob @Fromtheranks I'm not talking about individuals deciding how to apply the rules, as is often the case now.  I'm talking about adapting our organisational culture/s (presuming you're in another public sector org) so that Sir / Ma'am / Surname / Funny Hand Wave isn't the default, 'just because'.
full_text(utf-8): b"@beltfedgob @Fromtheranks I'm not talking about individuals deciding how to apply the rules, as is often the case now.  I'm talking about adapting our organisational culture/s (presuming you're in another public sector org) so that Sir / Ma'am / Surname / Funny Hand Wave isn't the default, 'just because'."

full_text:
@beltfedgob @Fromtheranks IMO, all that has a time and place (basic training and ceremonial).  Keep it there.

A bit like first names (should) have (more of) a time and place ;-)
full_text(utf-8): b'@beltfedgob @Fromtheranks IMO, all that has a time and place (basic training and ceremonial).  Keep it there.\n\nA bit like first names (should) have (more of) a time and place ;-)'

full_text:
@beltfedgob @Fromtheranks I've worked for some relatively senior people who've called me Rob, and I called them by their first name.  It made me feel a lot freer to say what I needed to say, when I needed to say it.

Again, it wouldn't work in all circumstances.  But in many it would.  Why blanket policy?
full_text(utf-8): b"@beltfedgob @Fromtheranks I've worked for some relatively senior people who've called me Rob, and I called them by their first name.  It made me feel a lot freer to say what I needed to say, when I needed to say it.\n\nAgain, it wouldn't work in all circumstances.  But in many it would.  Why blanket policy?"

full_text:
@beltfedgob @Fromtheranks But it's the 21st Century... and personally, it seems a weird and outdated blanket policy.

Don't get me started on saluting.
full_text(utf-8): b"@beltfedgob @Fromtheranks But it's the 21st Century... and personally, it seems a weird and outdated blanket policy.\n\nDon't get me started on saluting."

full_text:
@beltfedgob @Fromtheranks I'm not criticising hierarchy.  And I've seen first names go wrong (although the cultural problems were much broader and I doubt names would have contributed if it weren't 'a thing').

Cont'd.
full_text(utf-8): b"@beltfedgob @Fromtheranks I'm not criticising hierarchy.  And I've seen first names go wrong (although the cultural problems were much broader and I doubt names would have contributed if it weren't 'a thing').\n\nCont'd."

full_text:
@beltfedgob @Fromtheranks I'll try and dig out the study which found that calling people Sir and Ma'am led to a much greater reluctance to speak freely and thus poorer results during planning.

Cont'd.

full_text: I know that I have healed.  Now, when a train passes at high speed, I once again slightly involuntarily shiver.  That is my mind reminding me that I want to live.  And that, is a wonderful reminder indeed.
full_text(utf-8): b'I know that I have healed.  Now, when a train passes at high speed, I once again slightly involuntarily shiver.  That is my mind reminding me that I want to live.  And that, is a wonderful reminder indeed.'

full_text: If you are on the edge.  Please ask for help.  Dial one of the numbers below.  Speak to a friend.  Speak to a doctor.  Trust me.  It gets better.  I promise.
full_text(utf-8): b'If you are on the edge.  Please ask for help.  Dial one of the numbers below.  Speak to a friend.  Speak to a doctor.  Trust me.  It gets better.  I promise.'

full_text: Look after yourself, as well.  It‚Äôs gritty stuff and you‚Äôll need a release.
full_text(utf-8): b'Look after yourself, as well.  It\xe2\x80\x99s gritty stuff and you\xe2\x80\x99ll need a release.'

full_text: We, including you, are all only a few circumstances removed from the abyss.  Illnesses of the mind do not discriminate.  Even those at their lowest can be healed.  And even those not yet at their lowest might have contemplated what it would be like to step in front of that train.

And even those not yet at their lowest might have contemplated what it would be like to step in front of that train.'

full_text:
If you are not on the edge and somebody confides in you that they are:

Please.  They are desperate but they trust you.  Encourage them to ask for professional help.  Try not to judge them.  At least whilst in their presence.

full_text: A brief period taking anti-depressant medication was my run-flat, whilst Cognitive Behavioural Therapy enabled me to change my tyre.
full_text(utf-8): b'A brief period taking anti-depressant medication was my run-flat, whilst Cognitive Behavioural Therapy enabled me to change my tyre.'

full_text: I subsequently learned that passive suicidal ideations are a not unusual outcome of desperately wanting to escape one‚Äôs circumstances.  But getting help to improve one‚Äôs circumstances is the answer, rather than following through on the ultimate self-destructive impulse.
full_text(utf-8): b'I subsequently learned that passive suicidal ideations are a not unusual outcome of desperately wanting to escape one\xe2\x80\x99s circumstances.  But getting help to improve one\xe2\x80\x99s circumstances is the answer, rather than following through on the ultimate self-destructive impulse.'

full_text: Closer than I have ever been to the literal and metaphorical edge.  Staring into the abyss.  But not quite willing or able to step into it.  Yet.
full_text(utf-8): b'Closer than I have ever been to the literal and metaphorical edge.  Staring into the abyss.  But not quite willing or able to step into it.  Yet.'

full_text: Not actively preparing to jump.  But not entirely discounting the proposition.  A creeping interest.  An uncomfortable curiosity.  With the discomfort rapidly (and worryingly) decreasing.
full_text(utf-8): b'Not actively preparing to jump.  But not entirely discounting the proposition.  A creeping interest.  An uncomfortable curiosity.  With the discomfort rapidly (and worryingly) decreasing.'

full_text: So why am I stood on a train station platform, emotionally empty and psychologically numb, save for a macabre curiosity about how it would feel to step in front of the next passing train?
full_text(utf-8): b'So why am I stood on a train station platform, emotionally empty and psychologically numb, save for a macabre curiosity about how it would feel to step in front of the next passing train?'

full_text: Fast forward to late 2019.  I am a supposedly successful professional earning good money, married, and father of a beautiful newborn.  Life should be good.  Life should be more than good.
full_text(utf-8): b'Fast forward to late 2019.  I am a supposedly successful professional earning good money, married, and father of a beautiful newborn.  Life should be good.  Life should be more than good.'

full_text:
So I resorted to the trope of the uneducated or fearful or ignorant.  ‚ÄúSuicide.  How selfish‚Äù.

How little did I know‚Ä¶

full_text: More pressingly, I could not relate to these people.  They were clearly different to me.  Suicide was obviously ‚Äòvery sad‚Äô (duh), but not a problem that me or those like me would ever face.

full_text: It was beyond my understanding why they might think that, at best, instantaneous death, or at worst the prolonged agony caused by a mistimed jump would be preferable to going home that night to celebrate the dawn of a new decade.
full_text(utf-8): b'It was beyond my understanding why they might think that, at best, instantaneous death, or at worst the prolonged agony caused by a mistimed jump would be preferable to going home that night to celebrate the dawn of a new decade.'

full_text: I could not empathise with these other human beings who chose to end their existence by throwing themselves in front of several thousand tons of speeding metal.

The Abyss

2010.  I spent New Years Eve on a train.  A journey that should have taken three hours, took closer to seven or eight.  The reason?  En-route, in separate incidents, our train killed two people.  Each by their own design.

full_text:
It gets better. I promise.

#MentalHealthAwarenessWeek
full_text(utf-8): b'It gets better. I promise.\n\n#MentalHealthAwarenessWeek'

full_text:
(6) Don't give up.

Life afterwards is even better than life before. It sounds perverse, but you might even eventually miss the clarity that comes with the recovery process. More on that another time, perhaps. For now, please ask for help, and be kind to yourself.
full_text(utf-8): b"(6) Don't give up.\n\nLife afterwards is even better than life before. It sounds perverse, but you might even eventually miss the clarity that comes with the recovery process. More on that another time, perhaps. For now, please ask for help, and be kind to yourself."

full_text: Be kind to yourself (loads of practical advice available online, and from professionals including your doctor) and it will get better. I promise.
full_text(utf-8): b'Be kind to yourself (loads of practical advice available online, and from professionals including your doctor) and it will get better. I promise.'

full_text:
(5) Go easy on yourself.

You're healing. Which is amazing. And the kinder you are to yourself, the faster that process. You wouldn't run a marathon with a leg in plaster.
full_text(utf-8): b"(5) Go easy on yourself.\n\nYou're healing. Which is amazing. And the kinder you are to yourself, the faster that process. You wouldn't run a marathon with a leg in plaster."

full_text: But if they're talking to you about it, it's probably because they love you. They're emotionally invested, and they aren't professionals. So ask for professional help.
full_text(utf-8): b"But if they're talking to you about it, it's probably because they love you. They're emotionally invested, and they aren't professionals. So ask for professional help."

full_text:
(4) Go easy on your loved ones.

You'll need them and they need you to get better. I was a total dick at times, to my wife in particular. And yes - some friends and family give what seems like fucking stupid advice or unwarranted opinion.
full_text(utf-8): b"(4) Go easy on your loved ones.\n\nYou'll need them and they need you to get better. I was a total dick at times, to my wife in particular. And yes - some friends and family give what seems like fucking stupid advice or unwarranted opinion."

full_text:
Exactly the same as physical injury and illness, mental injury and illness doesn't just happen to other people. You deserve help.

You deserve help, and it gets better. I promise.
full_text(utf-8): b"Exactly the same as physical injury and illness, mental injury and illness doesn't just happen to other people. You deserve help.\n\nYou deserve help, and it gets better. I promise."

full_text:
(3) You deserve help.

My illness triggers were a combination of fairly common, long-term lifestyle factors as well as an unfortunate short-term succession of consecutive personal and professional traumas. The point being, it's really common. And that was pre Covid-19!
full_text(utf-8): b"(3) You deserve help.\n\nMy illness triggers were a combination of fairly common, long-term lifestyle factors as well as an unfortunate short-term succession of consecutive personal and professional traumas. The point being, it's really common. And that was pre Covid-19!"

full_text:
Perhaps use charities (personally - I found the Combat Stress and CALM helplines helpful, and the Warrior Course residential programme was excellent). Don't rely on booze.

Ask for help and then accept that help. It gets better. I promise.
full_text(utf-8): b"Perhaps use charities (personally - I found the Combat Stress and CALM helplines helpful, and the Warrior Course residential programme was excellent). Don't rely on booze.\n\nAsk for help and then accept that help. It gets better. I promise."

full_text: Tell your doctor and get medical help. Do some.. any... exercise (I chose boxing. Punching, and being punched in the face, can be wonderful).
full_text(utf-8): b'Tell your doctor and get medical help. Do some.. any... exercise (I chose boxing. Punching, and being punched in the face, can be wonderful).'

full_text: It's easy to default to 'people don't understand'. I do understand. I've been the one not wanting to leave the house or do any exercise or in-fact do anything whatsoever. Once you've taken the first steps it becomes so much easier. Trust me.
full_text(utf-8): b"It's easy to default to 'people don't understand'. I do understand. I've been the one not wanting to leave the house or do any exercise or in-fact do anything whatsoever. Once you've taken the first steps it becomes so much easier. Trust me."

full_text: In fact, off the top of my head I can't think of any physical injuries where recovery is an opportunity to actively become even better and stronger and more interesting and happier than before.
full_text(utf-8): b"In fact, off the top of my head I can't think of any physical injuries where recovery is an opportunity to actively become even better and stronger and more interesting and happier than before."

full_text:
(2) You need to help others help you.

Your mental injury / illness won't just get better if you ignore it. If you ignore it, it might kill you. If you help others to help you, you'll eventually thrive. You wouldn't ignore a rapidly growing lump.
full_text(utf-8): b"(2) You need to help others help you.\n\nYour mental injury / illness won't just get better if you ignore it. If you ignore it, it might kill you. If you help others to help you, you'll eventually thrive. You wouldn't ignore a rapidly growing lump."

full_text:
They were right. And I'm right. It might feel right now like you're stuck in a box with the walls of your mind closing in, but it won't always be that way. One day you'll be even more resilient and authentic than you were before you got ill. Trust me.

It gets better. I promise.
full_text(utf-8): b"They were right. And I'm right. It might feel right now like you're stuck in a box with the walls of your mind closing in, but it won't always be that way. One day you'll be even more resilient and authentic than you were before you got ill. Trust me.\n\nIt gets better. I promise."

full_text:
(1) It gets better. I promise.

I can clearly remember particular moments when I confided in friends what I was going through, and a LOT of them surprised me by saying that they'd also been there - or even worse - but that it gets better. Trust me.
full_text(utf-8): b"(1) It gets better. I promise.\n\nI can clearly remember particular moments when I confided in friends what I was going through, and a LOT of them surprised me by saying that they'd also been there - or even worse - but that it gets better. Trust me."

full_text: But I've been there. You might still think this shit advice - but at least hear me out :-)
full_text(utf-8): b"But I've been there. You might still think this shit advice - but at least hear me out :-)"

full_text: On which note, Mental Health Awareness Week begins tomorrow, and I want to share some advice - directly targeted at you, if you're suffering. You might be getting what you think is shit advice from people who don't understand because they haven't been there. Fair one.
full_text(utf-8): b"On which note, Mental Health Awareness Week begins tomorrow, and I want to share some advice - directly targeted at you, if you're suffering. You might be getting what you think is shit advice from people who don't understand because they haven't been there. Fair one."

full_text: I have undoubtedly had one of the easiest experiences of mental illness / injury in our society. Many others out there, possibly even you, are suffering through a far worse experience than I...
full_text(utf-8): b'I have undoubtedly had one of the easiest experiences of mental illness / injury in our society. Many others out there, possibly even you, are suffering through a far worse experience than I...'

full_text: 9 months later and my 'mild depressive episode' feels like distant history (largely due to a relatively short period of excellent psychiatric therapy, antidepressant medication, and the tonic of good friendship).
full_text(utf-8): b"9 months later and my 'mild depressive episode' feels like distant history (largely due to a relatively short period of excellent psychiatric therapy, antidepressant medication, and the tonic of good friendship)."

full_text: Close friends and family might jest that this was nothing new. The most frightening symptom of whatever-the-fuck-is-this-scary-thing-that-is-wrong-with-me was that I was struggling to love our baby daughter.
full_text(utf-8): b'Close friends and family might jest that this was nothing new. The most frightening symptom of whatever-the-fuck-is-this-scary-thing-that-is-wrong-with-me was that I was struggling to love our baby daughter.'

full_text: My memory and concentration were noticeably failing (I couldn't read a whole page of A4 and for months I hadn't been able to finish writing even just one email). I lacked any motivation, to the point of struggling to get out of bed.
full_text(utf-8): b"My memory and concentration were noticeably failing (I couldn't read a whole page of A4 and for months I hadn't been able to finish writing even just one email). I lacked any motivation, to the point of struggling to get out of bed."

full_text: I was genuinely shocked when the simplest, most-routine happenings went according to plan.
full_text(utf-8): b'I was genuinely shocked when the simplest, most-routine happenings went according to plan.'

full_text: Permanently angry, the slightest triggers would send me into embarrassing and exhausting spells of rage. I also became cripplingly cynical, defaulting to the assumption that all other people were at best incompetent, or more likely out to intentionally fuck me over.

'Sanguine'.

9 months ago I told my doctor that I was struggling. I think the actual words were "properly fucked".
